.TH IDLE 1 "June 2026" "idle" "IdleScreen CLI"
.SH NAME
idle \- control interface for the IdleScreen daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B idle
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B idle
is the CLI for controlling the idle-daemon screensaver monitoring service. It allows query of status, forcing transitions, toggling options, and previewing effects.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Print the active configuration and daemon status.
.TP
.B enable
Enable the idle-saver triggers.
.TP
.B disable
Disable the idle-saver triggers.
.TP
.B start
Trigger the idle saver now.
.TP
.B stop
Deactivate any active fullscreen screensaver presentation.
.TP
.BI preview " <saver> [--timeout N]"
Launch a plugin presentation preview in fullscreen. Pass \fB--timeout N\fR to auto-stop after N seconds.
.TP
.BI saver " set <name|random|shuffle>"
Set active screensaver plugin or enable randomizer shuffle mode.
.TP
.BI set-timeout " <minutes>"
Set the idle timeout in minutes.
.TP
.BI set-fps " <on|off>"
Enable or disable the FPS counter overlay.
.TP
.BI set-scale " <percentage>"
Set render scaling filter grid size (e.g. 50, 75, 100).
.TP
.B doctor [--fix] [--json]
Run system diagnostics on D-Bus, systemd, fonts, and active inhibitors. Pass \fB--fix\fR to auto-repair user units and directories.
.SH AUTHOR
IdleScreen <jerydleuck@gmail.com>
